<h2 id="about-the-project">About the project</h2>

<p>This is the project 3 of the Udacity/Google-FEND program. The purpose of this project is to practice utilizing the visual assets and a game loop engine tools (provided to clone <a href="https://github.com/udacity/frontend-nanodegree-arcade-game">here</a>) to add a number of entities to the game including the player characters and enemies to recreate the classic arcade game Frogger.</p>

<p><a href="https://matthewcranford.com/category/blog-posts/walkthrough/arcade-game/">Walk-through instructions</a> are provided to help succeeding the project.</p>

<p><a href="https://curious-yu.github.io/fend-arcade-game/">Click to Play the Game</a></p>

<h2 id="author">Author</h2>

<p>Udacity - initial work - <a href="https://github.com/udacity/frontend-nanodegree-arcade-game">frontend-nanodegree-arcade-game</a></p>

<p>Wen Yu - completing the game - <a href="https://curious-yu.github.io/fend-arcade-game/">frontend-nanodegree-arcade-game</a></p>

<h2 id="game-functionality">Game Functionality</h2>

<p>In this game you have a Player and Enemies (bugs). The goal of the player is to reach the water, without colliding into any one of the enemies.</p>

<ol>
  <li>The player can move left, right, up and down</li>
  <li>The enemies move at varying speeds on the paved block portion of the game board</li>
  <li>Once a the player collides with an enemy, the game is reset and the player moves back to the starting square</li>
  <li>Once the player reaches the water (i.e., the top of the game board), the game is won.</li>
</ol>

